parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt comes out of the door
the seat belt does not lock
the seat belt buckle fails
the seat belt releases during an accident
the seat belt does not restrain properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Seat Belt Recalls
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to repair seat belt recalls can lead to continued malfunction of the seat belt system, putting occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealership refuses to repair seat belt recall
parts are not available
repair is too expensive
dealership blames other components for the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails
the seat belt buckle does not lock
the seat belt buckle releases during an accident
the seat belt buckle is jammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in serious harm or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
often when shifting gears or applying the brakes
and may reach high speeds. The accelerator pedal may stick to the floor
and the engine may race or surge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause sudden acceleration, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stuck to the floor
making it difficult to control the vehicle's speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck idle speed solenoid can cause the engine to race or surge, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The engine RPM increases rapidly
and the vehicle may accelerate suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the transmission or shift control can cause sudden acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly when shifting gears
or the transmission may slip or hesitate
leading to unexpected speed changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage properly can cause the vehicle to roll backward on an incline, even when parked, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls backward on an incline when parked
transmission slips out of gear
vehicle moves unexpectedly when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure - Loss of Gear Engagement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage gears properly can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in a particular gear, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission slips out of gear
vehicle loses power
vehicle stalls
vehicle becomes stuck in a particular gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Axle breaks or cracks
vehicle loses control
oil pan punctures
steering linkage damage.
